OL,3,CFour-day weeks and driving limits: How
OL,4,Cthe world reacts to Iran oil crisis
OL,6,FThe vital Hormuz passage - which
OL,7,Ftypically see 200 oil and gas tankers
OL,8,Fpass through it on a normal day - has
OL,9,Fbeen effectively closed by the
OL,10,Fconflict between the US, Israel and
OL,11,FIran, with two fuel tankers struck
OL,12,Fnear the Iraqi port of Umm Qasr in the
OL,13,Fearly hours of Thursday.
OL,15,FMore than 30 countries agreed on
OL,16,FWednesday to release a record 400
OL,17,Fmillion barrels of reserve oil to
OL,18,Fcombat spiking prices, as others
OL,19,Fgrapple to save fuel and energy.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
